<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>verrucosus</i> is dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Cneoridium</i> <i>dumosum</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>scoparius</i>, <i>Malosma</i> <i>laurina</i>, <i>Rhus</i> <i>integrifolia</i>, <i>Salvia</i> <i>mellifera</i> and <i>Xylococcus</i> <i>bicolor</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 3 m; canopy is intermittent to continuous. Herbaceous layer is variable. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Slopes, ridges, and coastal terraces.  </div>
</div>

		
